---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import PreFooterCTA from '../../components/PreFooterCTA.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'How long does a metal roof last in Central Texas?',
    a: 'A properly installed metal roof by Lone Ranger Roofing in Temple, Killeen, or anywhere across Central Texas can last 50 years or more. Compared to asphalt shingles — which typically last 15-20 years in the Texas heat and hail corridor — metal roofing is often the last roof a homeowner ever installs.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What types of metal roofing does Lone Ranger Roofing install?',
    a: 'Lone Ranger Roofing installs standing seam, metal shingles, and R-panel metal roofing systems for residential and commercial properties across Temple, Killeen, Belton, Harker Heights, and the greater DFW area. We also offer over-roof installations where applicable. We\'ll recommend the right system based on your home, budget, and goals.',
  },
  {
    q: "What's the benefit of Lone Ranger Roofing having their own fabrication machine?",
    a: "Because Lone Ranger Roofing owns our own metal panel fabrication machine, we cut panels to exact measurements on-site rather than ordering from a third-party supplier. If a dimension needs to change, we adjust and cut right there — no reordering, no waiting on a delivery, no project delays. For homeowners in Temple, Killeen, and Central Texas, that means faster installs and a better-fitting finished roof.",
  },
  {
    q: 'Is metal roofing more expensive than asphalt shingles?',
    a: 'Yes, metal roofing has a higher upfront cost than asphalt shingles. However, when you factor in the 50+ year lifespan, lower maintenance costs, energy savings from heat reflection, and fewer storm damage repairs over time, most homeowners in Central Texas and DFW find that metal roofing costs less over the life of the roof. Lone Ranger Roofing also offers financing options to make the upfront investment more manageable.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can a metal roof be installed over my existing shingles?',
    a: "In some cases, yes. Lone Ranger Roofing can install a metal roof directly over existing asphalt shingles in Temple, Killeen, and surrounding Central Texas communities, which eliminates tear-off labor costs and speeds up installation. Not every roof is a good candidate — it depends on the existing deck condition, local building codes, and number of existing shingle layers. We'll assess during the free estimate and give you an honest answer.",
  },
  {
    q: 'How long does a residential metal roof installation take?',
    a: 'Most residential metal roof installations by Lone Ranger Roofing in Temple, Killeen, Belton, Harker Heights, and surrounding Central Texas communities are completed in a single day. Commercial metal roofing projects may take longer depending on size and scope — we\'ll give you a realistic timeline before the project starts so there are no surprises.',
  },
];

